docs.abstract: The trial of Paul Manafort in Alexandria, Va., has drawn an eclectic mix of lawyers, tourists and political junkies determined to witness a little piece of history.
docs.snippet: The trial of Paul Manafort in Alexandria, Va., has drawn an eclectic mix of lawyers, tourists and political junkies determined to witness a little piece of history.
docs.lead_paragraph: ALEXANDRIA, Va. — There are other activities better suited for 5 a.m., two strangers joked as they hunched in chairs against the wall of a courthouse. But this was the best way to guarantee a seat to watch the financial fraud trial of Paul Manafort — a case that has captured nationwide attention.

headline.main: Manafort Trial’s Spectators: ‘Why Go to Cancun’ When You Can See History?
headline.print_headline: Witnessing History at Manafort Trial, if You Can Stay Awake

headline.main: House Republican Campaign Committee Says It Was Hacked This Year
headline.print_headline: ‘Foreign Entity’ Is Said to Hack G.O.P. Officials
